article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- — Yaxel Lendeborg's 26 points helped UAB defeat North Texas 71-62 on Sunday. Lendeborg added eight rebounds and four blocks for the Blazers (17-8, 9-3 American Athletic Conference). Javian Davis scored 10 points and added three blocks. Efrem Johnson also had 10 points. Jason Edwards led the way for the Mean Green (14-11, 7-6) with 29 points and four assists. North Texas also got 13 points and four steals from Robert Allen. UAB took the lead with 7:04 to go in the first half and did not relinquish it. The score was 34-24 at halftime, with Lendeborg racking up 16 points. UAB was outscored by North Texas in the second half by a one-point margin, but still wound up on top. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
